This is a commercial litigation proceeding in federal court, with jurisdiction based on Federal Rule of Civil Procedure 8(a) and 28 U.S.C. §§ 1345 and 1348, as indicated in the Civil Cover Sheet (along with complaint)_7e7dea8d. The legal theories primarily involve federal antitrust law, specifically Section 2 of the Sherman Act, and California's Unfair Competition Law. The plaintiff, Epic Games, is seeking injunctive relief against Apple's alleged monopolistic maintenance and anti-competitive conduct in the iOS app distribution and in-app payment processing markets.

## Key Claims & Allegations
1.  **Sherman Act § 2 (Unlawful Monopoly Maintenance in the iOS App Distribution Market)**: Apple's conduct violates Section 2 of the Sherman Act by monopolizing the iOS App Distribution Market. (Complaint (Epic Games to Apple_7e646bdc, Pages: 47-47)
