## Strategic Assessment
This case presents significant legal issues concerning antitrust law and market dominance in the digital app distribution space. The primary legal challenge for Epic will be to prove Apple's anti-competitive conduct and the resulting harm, while Apple will likely defend its ecosystem as proprietary and necessary for security and user experience. Evidentiary strengths for Epic may lie in the widespread impact of Apple's policies on developers and consumers, while weaknesses could include the difficulty of defining relevant markets and proving anti-competitive intent. Immediate action items for the legal team would include a detailed review of the specific antitrust claims, discovery planning to gather evidence of market power and anti-competitive effects, and preparing for potential motions to dismiss or for preliminary injunctions.

